<br>
1] Ebayers can have a very negative affect on gameplay. While it is true that many of us could play the majority of EQ classes competantly with little or no previous experience in them, its also true that most of us have a great deal of in-game experience. After a while you learn the basics, and get a decent idea of aggro ranges, for instance, and know not to break mezzes, not to try to med in bad places, etc.<br>
<br>
Ebayed characters are easier to keep track of on FV because reputations are more significant, the population is so small, and because of the one-character-per-account rule. This isnt the case on blue servers... I remember grouping with a level 60 cleric in OS on a blue server about a year ago. After a few close calls we finally got wiped out, after which he admitted he had just bought the character and asked what the spell &quot;Courage&quot; did.<br>
<br>
We all thought he was joking, but it turned out he wasnt, because we then had to direct him to the correct rez spell. :P<br>
<br>
2] The &quot;ebayed characters&quot; issue will fade soon enough, because the market on characters will bottom out. There was a time when a well-equipped 50+ cleric was worth a few hundred dollars, but that time is past. As more people leave the game with the approach of Star Wars, etc. the market will become more flooded with high level characters, which will further drive the price down, until eventually it wont be worth bothering with the hassle.<br>
<br>
Equipment will continue to command decent prices for some time I believe, but characters will not.<br>
<br>
Domenic Dominion<br>
&quot;Some say the world will end in fire...&quot;<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/unakath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nakath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 254<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/16/02 2:47:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1561.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Truth about Ebay/PA/Web-sales</span><hr size=1> Background: I know people IRL who buy and sell accounts, gear and plat as a side job. I have taken hundreds of their characters out for test drives (playing a 60th level epic wiz for a night can be kinda fun if you're not getting anyone killed).<br>
<br>
I don't neccessarily feel this is wrong in and of itself... but what other people do with purchased characters is bad for the game and this is a large reason of why I stopped doing it. The other reason was that I didn't need the headaches of doing this because the government upped my student grant significantly.<br>
<br>
WHEN YOU SELL YOUR CHARACTER, THIS IS WHAT HAPPENS:<br>
<br>
First: they take everything droppable that isn't a quest item and all of your plat and they transfer it to their characters. THIS is what they bought your character for.<br>
<br>
Second: they go to EC (now the bazaar) and sell off all of your crap for plat en masse (/auc WTS 4 bags of stuff at torch one, /auc WTS 3 Lumberjack Caps for 100pp, etc).<br>
<br>
Third: They equip you out in easy to get nodrop stuff (moktor, hate armor, elysian, etc)<br>
<br>
Fourth: They finish any easy to finish quests on your character and sometimes change your name and level you up a bit. 49s become 51-2, 58-59s become 60s. If you're a few easy fightts with one uber group from your epic... they have an uber group to finish the epic.<br>
<br>
Fifth: They Re-Sell your character to a third party, with all of your info, usually for a little markup. These characters are RARELY seen on auction sites. These go out thru emailings or individual websites. Druids and Wizards go fast, en masse. Tradeskillers (esp 250 JC and Smithing) go pretty fast. Farmers go fast (Necros, Mages, high level Bards, high level Rangers).<br>
<br>
Sixth: (this is what they are in business for) They sell your droppable gear on their websites or on thier mailing lists and your plat to customers. Currently the Norrathian Platinum Piece is worth 1/100 of a US Dollar approximately. I think you can see how liquidation becomes VERY lucrative.<br>
<br>
Anyways... I hope this at least enlightened people to what is really going on (like a tour of a dairy!). <p><center>Nakath Thunderbush<BR>
